name: v0.6.20
body:
- Updated Travis configuration to test on latest Go releases.
- Updated dependencies to latest versions.
- Generated new code for `message.proto` from latest protoc-gen-go release.
- Updated `Makefile` to include `make proto`.

name: v0.6.19
body:
- Provides structured log output with `logrus`.
- Extended debug logging.
- Invalid blame reasons now drop the blamer.
- Update Access-Control headers for `/stats` endpoint to allow browser connections.

name: v0.6.18
body: - Don't add ip deny for passive disconnect, only increase ban score.

name: v0.6.17
body: - Fix regression in `CleanupDeniedByIPMatch`. Sever will now log and cleanup bans correctly.

name: v0.6.16
body:
- Add debug messages when DenyIP logic is applied.
- Fix linting recommendations from golint.

name: v0.6.15
body: - Lower denyIPTime to 5 minutes.

name: v0.6.14
body:
- Only allow a single shuffler to get banned per shuffle.
- Improved efficiency of broadcast logic.
- Simplified error handling in broadcast code.

name: v0.6.13
body:
- Only support single round shuffles. Removed N-1 support.
- Allow players to be blamed after disconnecting.
- Only allow unique verification keys to register.

name: v0.6.12
body: - Don't allow players to send messages to themselves.

name: v0.6.11
body: - Optimize blame reasons so they don't allocate on each message.

name: v0.6.9
body: - Isolate the accused instead of the blamer for IP deny logic.

name: v0.6.8
body:
- Added IP rate limits for TCP/WebSocket/HTTP endpoints.
- Removed `gvt` and moved to Go Modules.
- Now only supports Go 1.12. If your system has an older version of Go, please use the binary distribution.
- Dropped cross compiled binaries for unsupported builds in Travis.

name: v0.6.7
body: - Reduced deadlines to cleanup idle IPs.

name: v0.6.6
body:
- Optimized locks for bans.
- Included deny optimizations from @emergent-reasons.

name: v0.6.5
body: - Fixes incorrect mutex on `decreasePoolVoters`.

name: v0.6.4
body:
- Additional DoS protections. Users who are blamed out of a pool now won't be matched with those players when joining another pool.
- Added JSON output in debug mode.

name: v0.6.3
body: - Fix issue with pool assignment. Thanks @emergent-reasons!

name: v0.6.2
body:
- Improvements to ban logic.
- Errors from all listeners now get reported correctly.
- Extended deadlines for clients to support larger shuffle sizes.

name: v0.6.1
body: - Add support for a secondary Tor server.

name: v0.6.0
body:
- Added `version` to the announce message.
- Added server bans by IP for clients who are repeatedly blamed in pools.
- Updated stats to provide version information in pools, and ban score plus ban status for the requesting user.

name: v0.5.2
body: - Remove from tracker if registration errors.

name: v0.5.1
body: - Fix minor race where connection isn't cleaned up correctly. This resulted in a full pool that didn't clean up properly.

name: v0.5.0
body: - Add support for shuffle types. For now just DEFAULT/DUST.

name: v0.4.3
body: - Vendors the websocket library.

name: v0.4.2
body: - Added HTTP and TCP timeouts. TCP deadline is 2 minutes.

name: v0.4.1
body: Disable HTTP2, as it doesn't work for WebSockets.

name: v0.4.0
body: Adds support for WebSocket connections.

name: v0.3.5
body: Fixes locking issue in `broadcastNewRound`.

name: v0.3.4
body: Added `--bind-ip` flag to allow serving on only a particular interface.

name: v0.3.3
body:
- Fix panic from nil tracker data.
- Update default shuffle port to 1337.
- Enable stats port by default on 8080.

name: v0.3.2
body: - Adds `sufflePort` to stats JSON.

name: v0.3.1
body: Removes the sleep before broadcasting a reply now that the plugin parses the network stream correctly.

name: v0.3.0
body:
This is a breaking change to the protocol. Everyone should update their servers!

* Message framing has changed from [message][delimiter] to [magic][length][message] for all communications.https://github.com/cashshuffle/cashshuffle/pull/12

* Now supports multiple inputs for the shuffle! https://github.com/cashshuffle/cashshuffle/pull/11

name: v0.2.0
body: Added support to fetch certificates from LetsEncrypt!

name: v0.1.2
body: Updated message.proto file with latest from cashshuffle-electron-cash-plugin.

name: v0.1.1
body: This is a minor bug fix release to fix a panic when someone sends a message and immediately disconnects.

name: v0.1.0
body: Dev build of CashShuffle.
